description: At the tranquil end of a highly sought after east-side enclave, this classically elegant Circa 1912 residence radiates refined contemporary style inside and out. Masterfully renovated blended classic period features with contemporary updates, this solid double brick and sandstone home is set over two levels on dual land parcels totalling 2,225sqm.
- Classic entry hall with period details immediately impresses upon arrival
- Formal lounge with gas fireplace; high ceiling; picture rails; formal dining
- Inspiring timber kitchen with natural stone benchtop; quality appliances
- Open plan casual living and entertaining area with sunny atrium overlooking reserve
- Master bedroom with ensuite and walk-in robe
- Four additional bedrooms three with Juliet balconies; 6th bed/study
- Media room with built-in cabinetry and wet bar
- Sundrenched entertainment terrace; private established gardens
- 5-hole putting green; 2 x 10,000ltr water tanks; irrigation system
- Ducted air conditioning, ducted Ventis ventilation system; alarm
- Oversized double garaging with storage; additional off-street parking
headline: Classically elegant C1912 family residence on 2,225sqm land
